# DALL-E URL Handling

DALL-E 3 returns a temporary Azure blob storage URL (e.g. `https://oaidalleapiprodscus.blob.core.windows.net/...`). The URL works for two things:

1. Display in an `<img>` tag — works fine, browser fetches the image directly.
2. Pass to the vision API as `image_url` — the OpenAI API server fetches it server-side.

## Rule

**Never `fetch()` the DALL-E URL from the browser.** Never convert it to base64. Just use the URL string directly in both contexts.

The Azure blob URL has restrictive CORS that blocks browser-side `fetch`. Even if it didn't, doing so adds latency, doubles bandwidth, and serves no purpose — the vision API accepts URLs natively.

## Correct patterns

### Pipeline: pass URL string directly to vision

```typescript
// src/lib/pipeline.ts
const res = await openai.chat.completions.create({
  model: "gpt-4o-mini",
  messages: [
    {
      role: "user",
      content: [
        { type: "text", text: imageAnalysisPrompt(articleTypes) },
        { type: "image_url", image_url: { url: dalleUrl } },  // ✓ URL string
      ],
    },
  ],
  response_format: { type: "json_object" },
  temperature: 0.2,
});
```

### Display: use URL directly in img src

```tsx
// src/components/LoadingScreen.tsx and ResultsScreen.tsx
<img src={dalleImageUrl} alt="Style inspiration" />   {/* ✓ */}
```

## Anti-patterns

```typescript
// ❌ Fetching the URL client-side will fail with CORS error
const blob = await fetch(dalleUrl).then((r) => r.blob());

// ❌ Converting to base64 adds 30+ seconds for no benefit
const base64 = await blobToBase64(blob);
const visionInput = { type: "image_url", image_url: { url: `data:image/png;base64,${base64}` } };

// ❌ Downloading then re-serving via object URL
const objectUrl = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
<img src={objectUrl} />
```

## Lifetime

The DALL-E URL is valid for ~1 hour. The pipeline uses it twice (vision call, then UI display) within seconds of each other, so expiry is not a concern. Do not store the URL in localStorage or expect it to work later — for the demo, each run generates a fresh URL.
